## 6. Event-Driven Architecture (EDA)

Components communicate by **producing and consuming events asynchronously**. The producer doesn't know who consumes the events.

```
 +---------+      +-------------------+
 |Producer |----->|   Event Broker    |
 |(OrderSvc)|     |(Kafka/RabbitMQ)   |
 +---------+      +--------+----------+
                           |
          +----------------+----------------+
          |                |                |
     +----v---+      +----v--+      +---v------+
     |Shipping|      |Invoice|      |Analytics |
     +--------+      +-------+      +----------+
```

**Sub-patterns:**
- **Event Notification** — signals something happened
- **Event-Carried State Transfer** — event contains full state
- **Event Sourcing** — events ARE the source of truth

**When to use:** Decoupled systems, real-time processing, audit trails.

