## 7. Hexagonal Architecture (Ports & Adapters)

Keeps core application logic **independent from external systems** (UI, DB, APIs). Communication happens through defined ports and adapters.

```
+--------------------------------------+
|           ADAPTERS (outside)         |
| +------+  +------------------------+ |
| | REST |->|      PORT (interface)  | |
| |  UI  |  |                        | |
| +------+  |    CORE APPLICATION    | |
| |  CLI |->|  (pure business logic) | |
| +------+  |      PORT (interface)  | |
|           +------------------------+ |
|           ADAPTERS (outside)         |
+--------------------------------------+
```

**When to use:** Domain-focused apps, heavy testing requirements, swappable infrastructure.

