## 9. Domain-Driven Design (DDD)

By **Eric Evans**. Design centered around the domain model — a shared language between developers and domain experts.

```
+---------------------------------------------+
|               DOMAIN MODEL                  |
|                                             |
|  +----------------+  +-------------------+  |
|  |Bounded Context |  | Bounded Context   |  |
|  |   Ordering     |->|    Shipping       |  |
|  |                |  |                   |  |
|  | +----------+   |  | +-------------+  |  |
|  | |Aggregate |   |  | |  Aggregate  |  |  |
|  | | (Order)  |   |  | | (Shipment)  |  |  |
|  | +----------+   |  | +-------------+  |  |
|  +----------------+  +-------------------+  |
+---------------------------------------------+
```

**Building Blocks:**
- **Entity** — has identity (Order, User)
- **Value Object** — no identity (Money, Address)
- **Aggregate** — cluster of entities with one root

**When to use:** Complex business domains, large codebases, microservices with bounded contexts.

